[2026-05-09 19:13:01] --- T2 verdict ---
[2026-05-09 19:13:01]   CZ inequality L_lambda >= (1 - lambda)/(M - lambda) is
[2026-05-09 19:13:01]   consistent with arbitrary M > 1, since L_lambda <= 1 forces
[2026-05-09 19:13:01]   M >= 1 only. So CZ alone does NOT yield M > 1.
[2026-05-09 19:13:01]   CZ is in the WRONG DIRECTION for lower-bound on M.
[2026-05-09 19:13:01] --- T3. BMO/John-Nirenberg analysis (analytical) ---
[2026-05-09 19:13:01]   ||g||_BMO <= ||g||_inf / 2 = M/2 (trivial since g >= 0).
[2026-05-09 19:13:01]   John-Nirenberg: |{|g - g_I| > lambda}| <= C |I| exp(-c lambda / B).
[2026-05-09 19:13:01]   This gives UPPER BOUND on level sets, hence is
[2026-05-09 19:13:01]   CONSISTENT with arbitrary M and gives NO lower bound on M.
[2026-05-09 19:13:01]   Conclusion: BMO/JN is structurally in the wrong direction.
